<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<!--
    AppWidgetProviderInfo for the FRAME//LOG home screen widget.

    Three supported size configurations (SizeMode.Responsive in FrameLogWidget.kt):
      STANDARD — 4×2 cells (250×110dp): default placement, steppers side-by-side
      COMPACT  — 4×3 cells (250×180dp): taller, enlarged side-by-side steppers
      LOOSE    — 5×3 cells (320×180dp): taller + wider, stacked full-width steppers

    targetCellWidth/Height (API 31+): default placement size in the launcher (cell counts).
    minWidth/minHeight: legacy fallback for API 26–30; formula is (70n − 30)dp.
      4 cells wide:  70 × 4 − 30 = 250dp
      2 cells tall:  70 × 2 − 30 = 110dp

    maxResizeWidth/maxResizeHeight (API 31+): caps the resize handle.

    PIXEL 7 NOTE — launcher row height is ~74dp (vs the standard 70dp formula).
    This matters for maxResizeHeight:
      Standard formula:  3 rows = 70 × 3 − 30 = 180dp
      Pixel 7 actual:    3 rows = 74 × 3 − 30 = 192dp
    Setting maxResizeHeight to the standard-formula value (180dp) leaves Pixel 7
    users 12dp short of the 3-row snap point — the resize handle can't reach it.
    maxResizeHeight is set to 250dp to clear 3 rows on any launcher.

    Column width on Pixel 7 follows the standard 70dp formula: 5 columns = 320dp,
    which matches maxResizeWidth exactly and snaps correctly to the 5-cell boundary.

    resizeMode="horizontal|vertical": allows the user to resize in both axes so all
    three size variants are reachable on the home screen.

    updatePeriodMillis = 0: all widget updates are pushed explicitly by
    FrameLogWidgetUpdater (after frame log, roll switch, and widget add/enable).
    Android's minimum interval is 30 minutes — far too slow for a shot logger.

    initialLayout references glance_default_loading_layout from the glance-appwidget
    library, which shows a blank surface while Glance initialises the first render.
-->
<appwidget-provider xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"
    android:minWidth="250dp"
    android:minHeight="110dp"
    android:targetCellWidth="4"
    android:targetCellHeight="2"
    android:maxResizeWidth="320dp"
    android:maxResizeHeight="250dp"
    android:resizeMode="horizontal|vertical"
    android:updatePeriodMillis="0"
    android:initialLayout="@layout/glance_default_loading_layout"
    android:description="@string/widget_description"
    android:widgetCategory="home_screen" />
